Prepare cornbread stuffing mix according to package directions. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place sausage in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown; drain. In a large bowl, mix cornbread stuffing, sausage, onion, celery, butter, poultry seasoning and desired amount of chicken broth. Transfer mixture to a medium baking dish. Cover, and bake 30 minutes in the preheated oven, until lightly browned.